    "narrative": "For April 8, 2026, the Ghost Ride the WHIP optimizer highlights **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (78.25) and **Mickey Moniak** (75.98) as our primary drivers of production against Luis Severino and Cristian Javier, respectively. **Chisholm Jr.** benefits immensely from the 15% SP skill boost provided by Severino, and **Moniak** is our standout play of the day, capitalizing on a 14% park factor boost and a massive 14% dynamic platoon advantage while batting second. **James Wood** (73.87) also projects as an elite start; hitting leadoff against Michael McGreevy provides the high-floor environment we covet to keep our Roto pace consistent, especially in the scarce SB category.\n\nOur most difficult decision came at the utility spot, where **Vinnie Pasquantino** (46.57) ultimately fell short of a start. While he carries a respectable base, his struggles against left-handed pitching (Cantillo) and the lack of a clear platoon edge forced us to pivot toward the higher efficiency of **Moniak**. We remain wary of the volatility at the bottom of the order; **Kyle Karros** (54.54) and **Jose Caballero** (56.24) are both in the \"marginal\" territory today. **Karros** is saddled with a significant 8% penalty due to his likely #9 spot in the lineup, while **Caballero** faces a steep 13% platoon penalty despite the favorable matchup against Severino. Please monitor the official lineup cards closely for **Gabriel Moreno**, **Tyler Soderstrom**, and **Corbin Carroll**; while **Carroll** holds a solid 63.31 score, his -6% dynamic platoon penalty against David Peterson warrants a watchful eye if the wind patterns at the park shift before first pitch.",
